Mode SQL generated <code>append</code> <code>INSERT INTO table (cols) VALUES (chunk of 1,000 rows)</code> Auto-upgrades to <code>LOAD DATA LOCAL INFILE</code> for &gt; 10,000 rows if <code>local_infile=ON</code> <code>replace</code> <code>REPLACE INTO table (cols) VALUES (chunk of 1,000 rows)</code> <code>upsert</code> <code>INSERT INTO table (cols) VALUES … ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE col=VALUES(col)…</code> <p>Enabling LOAD DATA LOCAL INFILE</p> <p><pre><code>SET GLOBAL local_infile = 1;
-- or in my.cnf: local_infile=1
</code></pre> If disabled, PardoX automatically falls back to chunked INSERT and logs a notice to stderr.</p>
